Nakuru East MP David Gikaria on Monday had his fingerprints taken by the DCI to allow a case against him to proceed. The prosecution had said the MP had initially refused to have his fingerprints taken. The Nakuru High Court ordered him to present himself before the Directorate of Criminal Investigations or risk arrest. Gikaria was charged with demolishing a perimeter wall on land belonging to Ense Ltd, claiming it is owned by Naka Primary School. The land is in Nakuru Town East subcounty. Gikaria is accused of destroying property worth Sh13 million on May 29. He was also accused of stealing 300 wheelbarrows, 500 pipes and four water tanks valued at Sh2 million.